  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>dried cranberries</strong>, 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span><strong> sugar</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[550ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong> to a pot over a medium-low heat </p>\n<p>Cook for 25-30 min or until the cranberries have broken down and the sauce is beginning to thicken</p>\n<p>Tip: Crush the cranberries with a back of a spoon to help break them down</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, slice the <strong>Chantenay</strong> <strong>carrots</strong> in half lengthways</p>\n<p>Cut 1 <span class=\"text-danger\">[2] </span>piece<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> of <strong>baking paper</strong> (or tin foil) approx. the size of an A3 sheet of paper</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>carrots</strong> and <strong>cloves</strong> to the centre of the baking paper </p>\n<p>Tip: If you're cooking for 4, you'll need to make two parcels! </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Scrunch the edges of the <strong>baking paper</strong> together around the carrots to form a sealed parcel – these are your <strong>en</strong> <strong>papillote carrots</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: En papillote is French for \"enveloped in paper\"</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Line a baking tray (or two!) with <strong>tin foil</strong> and add the <strong>baby gammon joint<span class=\"text-danger\">[s] </span></strong>to one side of the tray</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>en papillote carrots</strong> to the other side of the tray</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 30 min or until the gammon is cooked through</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> and chop them into large, bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot with plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong> and a generous pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 12-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once done, drain and return to the pot to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the cranberries have broken down, add a knob of <strong>butter</strong> to the pot with a pinch of<strong> pepper </strong>and gently stir it all together until the sauce has reached a gravy-like consistency - this is your <strong>cranberry gravy</strong></p>\n<p>Tip: Add a splash of water if the sauce is looking a little thick!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> drained potatoes</strong> to a low heat with a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Mash until smooth and season with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and<strong> pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Stir the<strong> wholegrain mustard </strong>through the mash – this is your<strong> mustard mash</strong></p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC1831Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> roast ham</strong> finely</p>\n<p>Serve the <strong>sliced ham</strong> over the <strong>mustard</strong> <strong>mash</strong> with the <strong>en papillote carrots</strong> and <strong>cranberry gravy</strong> to the side</p>\n<p>Tip: Remove the cloves from your carrots before serving</p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
